================
HOW TO PATCH VLC
================

Tested with vlc git version (2010-06-04)

1. Get vlc source from repository:

	git clone git://git.videolan.org/vlc.git --depth 1
	
2. Change into vlc/ directory and apply the patch:

	cd vlc
	git apply vlc_bluray.patch

3. Configure vlc and build it 

	./bootstrap
	mkdir build && cd build 
	../configure --enable-bluray
	make

4. Install all files with make install

	sudo make install

5. Run vlc passing it a bluray:// url as follows:

	vlc bluray://</path/to/disc>:<title>
	
	e.g.
	
	vlc bluray:///mnt/BLURAY_DISC:1	(<-- to play 00001.m2ts on disc /mnt/BLURAY_DISC)


NOTE:
Before running vlc, you can turn off all libbluray debug messages using 'export BD_DEBUG_MASK=0'.
This will help with performance and clean up your terminal.
